Hummingbird Ardublock Installer
A simple application to enable easy installation of Ardublock with the Hummingbird libraries.
-----------------------------------
To run:
Install the Arduino IDE from your distribution's repositories or arduino.cc.

Run it at least once.

Then, return to this folder and click run.sh to run the installer. You may have to set run.sh to be executable by doing chmod +x ./run.sh or by using your file manager.

Click on the install button to copy the files into the correct directories.